 {"id":"bd-1ru.9","title":"Add feedback field to robot-triage output","description":"Go's bv-90 feature adds a feedback object to robot-triage output containing the current feedback loop state: recent accepts/ignores per issue, weight adjustments derived from feedback, and model version. This enables agents to understand how their past feedback influenced current recommendations. IMPLEMENTATION: (1) Requires the feedback loop system to be implemented first (dependency). (2) After feedback is available, add feedback: Option<FeedbackState> to robot-triage output in main.rs. (3) Serialize current feedback stats. Go ref: feedback.go (FeedbackData, FeedbackEvent, WeightAdjustment), main.go ~line 3025 (feedback field). ACCEPTANCE: --robot-triage includes feedback object when feedback data exists, null/absent otherwise.","status":"closed","priority":3,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:55:20.572322202Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-03-09T03:56:12.522926421Z","closed_at":"2026-03-09T03:56:12.522439369Z","close_reason":"Added optional feedback field to RobotTriageOutput. Includes FeedbackStats (total_accepted, total_ignored, avg scores, weight adjustments) when feedback events exist. Omitted via skip_serializing_if when no feedback recorded. 474 lib tests pass.","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0,"dependencies":[{"issue_id":"bd-1ru.9","depends_on_id":"bd-1ru","type":"parent-child","created_at":"2026-03-07T23:55:20.572322202Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-1ru.9","depends_on_id":"bd-1ru.1","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:40:46.871349241Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""},{"issue_id":"bd-1ru.9","depends_on_id":"bd-3ud","type":"blocks","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:04:29.418999445Z","created_by":"ubuntu","metadata":"{}","thread_id":""}],"comments":[{"id":13,"issue_id":"bd-1ru.9","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"Go reference: pkg/analysis/triage.go — feedback field in triage output shows any user-applied score adjustments, so consumers can see 'this item was manually boosted by +0.3 because domain expert said so'. BLOCKED BY bd-3ud (feedback system).","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:06:20Z"},{"id":70,"issue_id":"bd-1ru.9","author":"Dicklesworthstone","text":"TESTING REQUIREMENT: This task is NOT complete until it includes inline unit tests (#[cfg(test)] mod tests) that verify: (1) the new fields serialize correctly to JSON, (2) default/missing values handle gracefully, (3) the field type matches Go's output. Tests must be in the same file as the implementation.","created_at":"2026-03-08T00:37:14Z"}]}
